Understanding the TCP-IP suite

TCP/IP Suite or Internet Suite

A set of protocols that allows us to communicate and exchange data on the network

Defines how data is packetized, addressed, transmitted, and routed


The key protocols are - TCP,UDP,IP,ICMP

Network Layer
The main players are IP and ICMP

Internet Protocol - Responsible for routing and addressing
Internet Control Messaging Protocol - Provides error, routing, and control messages


Transport Layer
Provides data transport

TCP - connection-oriented
UDP - connectionless
